Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the project
=================================================

Changes Made:
-------------

1. Installed @vercel/analytics package
   - Added @vercel/analytics@2.0.1 to dependencies using pnpm
   - Package manager: pnpm (as indicated by pnpm-lock.yaml in the project)

2. Modified src/App.jsx
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
   - Added <Analytics /> component at the end of the App component (before the closing div)
   - Following React-specific instructions from official Vercel documentation

3. Updated package files
   - package.json: Added @vercel/analytics to dependencies
   - pnpm-lock.yaml: Updated with new dependencies

Implementation Details:
-----------------------

Framework: Vite + React (identified from vite.config.js and React imports)
Documentation Source: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart (fetched latest version)

The Analytics component was placed at the end of the main App component's JSX tree,
right after the footer and before the closing </div> tag. This ensures analytics 
tracking is loaded on all pages since App.jsx is the root component.

Verification:
-------------

✅ Build completed successfully (pnpm build)
✅ Linter passed with 0 errors and 0 warnings (pnpm lint)
✅ No breaking changes introduced
✅ All dependencies properly installed

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for React projects 
and maintains the existing code structure and patterns.

Next Steps:
-----------

After deployment to Vercel, you'll need to:
1. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Navigate to the Analytics section to view visitor data
